## Decisions and Action Items

*   **Attestation TLS Vulnerability**: The security vulnerabilities discovered in the confidential computing attested TLS protocol (CV-7.5) will be officially reported to the relevant working groups.
*   **Post-Quantum SSH Key Formats**: A gap was identified in the draft specifications because the private key format for ML-DSA keys in SSH is currently undefined. This issue will be brought to the SSH working group session for resolution.
*   **MUD Specification Bug**: The bug identified by **Elliot** during MUD Maker testing will be communicated to the working group for correction in the active drafts.
*   **NTS Pool Bug**: The IPv4/IPv6-mapped address handling bug in NTS pools will be addressed by the NTP working group.

